(366, 6, 'Episode 6', '2016-02-07', 'As Napoleon marches into Moscow, the Rostovs rush to leave the city.'),
(367, 1, 'Episode One', '2010-09-26', 'Downton Abbey is a historical drama written by Julian Fellowes. The series follows the lives of the Crawley family and the servants who work for them in an Edwardian country house just after the turn of the 20th century.'),
(367, 2, 'Episode Two', '2010-10-03', 'Matthew Crawley and his mother Isobel arrive at Downton, and have difficulty settling in. Carson is mortified when confronted by his past. Violet attempts to promote a match between Matthew and Mary. Isobel is elected to serve on the hospital board.');
INSERT INTO `tv_episode_detail` (`id`, `episode`, `name`, `release_date`, `overview`) VALUES
(367, 3, 'Episode Three', '2010-10-10', 'Cora''s tries to set up Mary with Evelyn Napier, who falls for his friend instead, with significant consequences for the household. Bates takes action to help cure his limp.'),
(367, 4, 'Episode Four', '2010-10-17', 'Mrs Hughes finds herself the focus of speculation when she meets a former suitor who makes her question her position. Violet and Isobel clash over a medical ailment affecting Molesley. Carson is concerned there is a thief at work in the grounds.'),
(367, 5, 'Episode Five', '2010-10-24', 'Isobel finds herself at odds with Violet. Mary is introduced to a potential suitor but wants to be with Matthew. Anna works out who stole a valuable snuff box. O''Brien plans a way for Edith to get even with Mary.'),
(367, 6, 'Episode Six', '2010-10-31', 'Sybil puts herself in danger when a fight breaks out. Sybil''s sisters notice Matthew''s feelings for her. Mary is surprised by a marriage proposal. Bates clears his name over the missing wine but resigns rather than name the real culprit.'),
(367, 7, 'Episode Seven', '2010-11-07', 'Cora''s pregnancy throws the inheritance issue into doubt. Matthew must  wait for an answer to his wedding proposal. O''Brien discovers more compromising information about Bates. Thomas leaves.'),
(368, 1, 'A Father''s Great Expectations', '2011-04-03', 'The Kennedys rally to put Jack in the White House, but their difficult past illuminates a deeper struggle.\n\nâ€œPeople talk about the curse that seems to echo down the generations of the Kennedys and in a certain sense itâ€™s true,â€ says Tom Wilkinson. â€œAnd if you are going to see it in the kind of Greek tragedy sense, there isnâ€™t a better sort of patriarchal figure than Joe Kennedy because his world view was extreme. His world view was: ambition, money and family. Itâ€™s almost medieval in its simplicity â€¦ but almost everything else went by the boards.â€\n\n-Tom Wilkinson'),
(368, 2, 'Shared Victories, Private Struggles', '2011-04-03', 'The Presidential election comes down to the wire; Bobby tells Joe Sr. heâ€™s leaving politics.\n\nâ€œJohn F. Kennedy was a very complicated person who meant a lot of things to a lot of different people. I have my own interpretation of who he was and what his legacy was. Kennedy served as President of the United States during an extraordinary period of time and brought us exceptional social and political changes in a short time, in 1000 days. He gave this country a sense of purpose and enthusiasm which was much needed at that time.â€\n\n- Greg Kinnear'),
(368, 3, 'Failed Invasion, Failed Fidelity', '2011-04-05', 'When the Bay of Pigs invasion proves disastrous, JFK makes a difficult decision he must later atone for.\n\nâ€œJohn F. Kennedy changed the image of the United States when he was president. People around the world remember that time and remember the days when America was the leading shining light for freedom and democracy, which was represented so well by Kennedy at the time.â€\n\n- Executive Producer Michael Prupas'),
(368, 4, 'Broken Promises and Deadly Barriers', '2011-04-06', 'When the Bay of Pigs invasion proves disastrous, JFK makes a difficult decision he must later atone for. â€œJohn F. Kennedy changed the image of the United States when he was president. People around the world remember that time and remember the days when America was the leading shining light for freedom and democracy, which was represented so well by Kennedy at the time.â€ - Executive Producer Michael Prupas'),
(368, 5, 'Moral Issues and Inner Turmoil', '2011-04-07', 'Riots over desegregation in the South force JFK to act; Jackieâ€™s use of amphetamines continues; Joe Sr. suffers a stroke.\n\nâ€œJack and Jackie Kennedy were truly the king and queen of America at the time. They were called Americaâ€™s royalty because they wereâ€¦But as beautiful as they looked, and as trouble free as they seemed, underneath there was always another more troubled layer.â€\n\n- Director Jon Cassar'),
(368, 6, 'On the Brink of War', '2011-04-08', 'The Cuban missile crisis brings America and Russia to the brink of war; Jackie leaves JFK after one infidelity too many.\n\nâ€œThe lasting legacy of Jack and Bobby Kennedy was to resolve political crisis with the least amount of bloodshed possibleâ€¦We never went to war with the Soviet Union. Had that crisis not been handled the way it was, we wouldnâ€™t be here. This planet would be dead. Everything else pales to insignificance compared to that.â€\n\n- Writer Stephen Kronish'),
(368, 7, 'The Countdown to Tragedy', '2011-04-10', 'Jack and Jackie suffer the loss of their newborn child; she and JFK are in Dallas on that fateful day in November.\n\nâ€œThereâ€™s an arc of the love story through the whole eight episodes. In episode seven [after the death of their newborn son], theyâ€™ve really started to reconnect. Theyâ€™ve had their ups and downs and at the point where you think that they can live happily ever after, the unfortunate happens.â€\n\n- Director Jon Cassar'),
(368, 8, 'The Aftermath: A Family''s Curse of Misfortune and Heartbreak', '2011-04-10', 'Bobby blames himself for his brotherâ€™s death. Five years later, tragedy strikes again.\n\nâ€œI admire Robert Kennedy because of his courage to stand up during an extremely volatile and difficult time in America, knowing full well what might happen to him.  RFK lived and died as a passionate advocate of peace, justice and equality and he believed in compassion toward fellow human beings, not only in the United States, but all over the world.  I believe he would have made an extraordinary President.  Now, more than ever, the world is in need of men like Robert Kennedy.â€\n\n- Barry Pepper'),
(369, 1, 'Pilot', '2011-09-22', 'When the social security number of a young prosecutor comes up, Reese and Finch work together to figure out if their person of interest is the victim or perpetrator.'),
(369, 2, 'Ghosts', '2011-09-28', 'Reese and Finch question the machine''s reliability when they are asked to investigate a teenager who was killed years earlier; Finch remembers the origin of the machine.'),
(369, 3, 'Mission Creep', '2011-10-03', 'Reese goes undercover to find the threat surrounding the next person on Finch''s list: a young army veteran named Joey Durban.'),
(369, 4, 'Cura Te Ipsum', '2011-10-13', 'Reese and Finch get some help from Detective Fusco  as they surveil their latest POI, Dr. Megan Tillman, while sheâ€™s on call and after hours to unravel the threat surrounding the promising young physician.'),
(369, 5, 'Judgement', '2011-10-20', 'Reese and Finch have the added challenge of investigating a Person of Interest who wants nothing to do with their brand of vigilante justice.'),
(369, 6, 'The Fix', '2011-10-27', 'Reese becomes romantically involved with the newest Person of Interest: an attractive woman who isn''t all that she seems.'),
(369, 7, 'Witness', '2011-11-03', 'The Machine identifies a school teacher who witnessed a mob hit as their next POI and Reese and Finch rush to save his life.'),
(369, 8, 'Foe', '2011-11-17', 'When Reese and Finch discover that their latest POI has connections to Cold War Soviet espionage circles, they quickly learn how covert ops were handled in a world before The Machine.'),
(369, 9, 'Get Carter', '2011-12-08', 'Reese and Finchâ€™s game of cat and mouse with Detective Carter becomes infinitely more complicated when The Machine declares that she is their newest POI.'),
(369, 10, 'Number Crunch', '2011-12-15', 'As Detective Carter deals with the fallout from her recent encounter with Reese and Finch, The Machine ups the ante for the duo by giving them four Social Security numbers instead of one.'),
(369, 11, 'Super', '2012-01-12', 'Reese is confined to a wheelchair recovering from his gunshot wound, but Finch sets him up in an apartment where heâ€™s to keep an eye on the Super, who is their latest POI. Also, Finch approaches Carter and gives her a POI to show her what they do.'),
(369, 12, 'Legacy', '2012-01-19', 'When Carter finally comes face-to-face with Reese, he urges her to join forces to help with their latest POI, a scrappy young woman from the wrong side of the tracks who turned her life around and became a lawyer.'),
(369, 13, 'Root Cause', '2012-02-02', 'The Machine gives Reese and Finch the number of a down-and-out man who has been pushed too far, and they''re forced to turn to former Person of Interest Zoe Morgan for help.'),
(369, 14, 'Wolf and Cub', '2012-02-09', 'The Machine identifies Darren, a teenager whose brother was just murdered, as the next POI. Meanwhile, Finch is growing concerned that the son of his former business partner is dangerously close to finding out about the Machine.'),
(369, 15, 'Blue Code', '2012-02-16', 'Reese discovers thereâ€™s more to the story after he infiltrates a smuggling ring to get close to his latest POI.'),
(369, 16, 'Risk', '2012-02-23', 'The Machine leads Reese and Finch to Wall Street when a sharp young trader at a major investment bank becomes embroiled in a multi-million dollar financial scam.'),
(369, 17, 'Baby Blue', '2012-03-08', 'When The Machine spits out the number of a 6-month-old baby, Reese and Finch turn into overly protective parents â€“ with an arsenal at their disposal. Meanwhile, when Elias resurfaces, Detective Carter begins to question her new allegiance with Reese and Finch'),
(369, 18, 'Identity Crisis', '2012-03-29', 'The Machine''s latest number presents a unique challenge for Reese and Finch since the person has virtually no digital footprint - and appears to be leading a double life.'),
(369, 19, 'Flesh and Blood', '2012-04-05', 'When The Machine spits out five numbers, naming the Don of each of New Yorkâ€™s crime families, Reese and Finch suspect Elias is planning to eliminate his competition.'),
(369, 20, 'Matsya Nyaya', '2012-04-26', 'Reese goes undercover as an armored car company employee, and faces memories from his past with the CIA.'),
(369, 21, 'Many Happy Returns', '2012-05-03', 'Finch gives Reese his birthday off so that his partner doesn''t have to face a Number that is tied to Reese''s past.'),
(369, 22, 'No Good Deed', '2012-05-10', 'The newest POIâ€™s curiosity could spell his doom when he finds himself embroiled in a dark government conspiracy â€“ one that Finch is all too familiar with. Meanwhile, Reese uncovers something revealing about Finchâ€™s past.'),
(369, 23, 'Firewall', '2012-05-17', 'As the clock ticks down, Reese winds up trapped with his POI in the most heavily surveilled part of the city, forced to rely on the help of Finch, Carter and Fusco to fend off the FBI, corrupt cops and a slew of old foes.'),
(370, 1, 'I.', '2014-01-25', 'Whilst facing threats on all sides, including a possible mutiny, Captain Flint hires a young sailor named John Silver, who hides his most precious possession. As the Royal Navy gets ever more powerful, Eleanor keeps order on New Providence.'),
(370, 2, 'II.', '2014-02-01', 'Flint discovers a thief amongst his crew. Eleanor must make a difficult decision. John hides with Max, inside a brothel.'),
(370, 3, 'III.', '2014-02-08', 'While Flint and Gates realise they need help to find the Urca d''Lima, John and Billy have to increase the crew''s morale. Vane impresses Eleanor and Gates receives a promotion.'),
(370, 4, 'IV.', '2014-02-15', 'Captain Flint is warned about Billy. Vane encounters someone from his past. Eleanor asks her father for help. The crew of The Walrus suffer a disastrous undertaking.'),
(370, 5, 'V.', '2014-02-22', 'Bonny confesses. Rackham makes a life-altering decision. Richard forces Eleanor''s hand. A chess match is organized for Flint and the Walrus crew.'),
(370, 6, 'VI.', '2014-03-01', 'Chasing the Andromache is a pricey endeavor. Eleanor needs help from Silver. Billy believes Gates should confront Flint. Bonny takes a stand.'),
(370, 7, 'VII.', '2014-03-08', 'Flint comes clean with Gates. Randall''s actions cause problems for Silver. Eleanor suffers a loss. Max helps Rackham. Vane faces his biggest challenge.'),
(370, 8, 'VIII.', '2014-03-15', 'The hunt for the Urca begins. Things change for Eleanor. Bonny and Rackham are haunted by their past sins.'),
(371, 1, 'IX.', '2015-01-24', 'The Walrus crew is stranded, with an army of Spanish soldiers standing between them and the precious Urca gold. With their crimes against their brethren no longer a secret, Flint and Silver must join forces in a desperate bid for survival.'),
(371, 2, 'X.', '2015-01-31', 'Flint gives Dufresne some advice. Silver must make himself indispensable. Eleanor is asked to depose a captain. Rackham gets ambitious.'),
(371, 3, 'XI.', '2015-02-07', 'Flint returns to Nassau and encounters a dilemma. Eleanor turns to an unlikely source for help. Rackham works to restore his reputation. Vane gets an unexpected prize.'),
(371, 4, 'XII.', '2015-02-14', 'Flint threatens Vane. Eleanor chooses a side. Rackham learns what Max is capable of. Silver reunites with an old friend.'),
(371, 5, 'XIII.', '2015-02-21', 'Miranda endeavors to save the island. Eleanor sees old wounds reopened. Rackham is on the scent of a secret. Vane is forced to take matters into his own hands.'),
(371, 6, 'XIV.', '2015-02-28', 'Eleanor mediates a peace. Rackham learns a hard lesson. Flint goes back on a promise. Bonny goes out of control.'),
(371, 7, 'XV.', '2015-03-07', 'Max surveys the aftermath of a massacre. News from the outside world impacts Flint and Silver. Eleanor takes a risk that she hopes secures her future. Bonny comes to a crossroads. Dufresne provokes Billy to act.'),
(371, 8, 'XVI.', '2015-03-14', 'Flint and Miranda prepare for a tough go of it. Silver becomes enlightened. Eleanor learns Max''s secret. Vane makes a move.'),
(371, 9, 'XVII.', '2015-03-21', 'Flint and Miranda come to grips with their past. Bonny makes clear her intentions to Rackham. Vane collects a huge prize. Eleanor issues a declaration of war.'),
(371, 10, 'XVIII.', '2015-03-28', 'Flint acquires an unlikely ally. Vane''s crew seeks a sea change. Silver makes a sacrifice.'),
(372, 1, 'Deadwood', '2004-03-21', 'Former Montana marshal Seth Bullock starts a hardware business for miners, and the arrival of Wild Bill Hickok creates a stir. Meanwhile, a corrupt saloon owner brokers a land claim for a wealthy New Yorker.'),
(372, 2, 'Deep Water', '2004-03-28', 'Calamity Jane helps Doc protect a young girl who survived a recent massacre. New Yorker Brom Garret realizes he may not be cut out for prospecting. Dan mulls over a difficult order from Al Swearengen.'),
(372, 3, 'Reconnoitering the Rim', '2004-04-04', 'Believing he''s been duped, Brom Garret threatens to call the Pinkertons on Swearengen. Star and Bullock finally reach a deal on their hardware-store property. A new gambling outfit arrives from Chicago.'),
(372, 4, 'Here Was a Man', '2004-04-11', 'Alma asks Hickok to investigate the tragic fallout of her husband''s gold claim purchase. McCall plots revenge after being humiliated at poker. Charlie Utter departs camp for Cheyenne. Doc Cochran makes a house call to the Bella Union.'),
(372, 5, 'The Trial of Jack McCall', '2004-04-18', 'The town buries its most famous casualty while the man responsible is tried in Swearengen''s saloon. Trixie helps a widowed Alma care for an orphan. Doc warns of an impending epidemic.'),
(372, 6, 'Plague', '2004-04-25', 'Bullock''s form of vigilante justice meets resistance from the locals. The town fathers band together to fight an epidemic. Farnum reluctantly agrees to keep an eye on Alma and Trixie. Swearengen adds journalist to his colorful rÃ©sumÃ©.'),
(372, 7, 'Bullock Returns to the Camp', '2004-05-02', 'Bullock''s vigilantism makes new enemies. Utter returns to Deadwood to say goodbye to an old friend. Teenage siblings arrive on a quest to find their father. Alma holds on to her late husband''s claim despite another offer from Farnum.'),
(372, 8, 'Suffer the Little Children', '2004-05-09', 'A much-needed vaccine arrives in Deadwood. There are rumblings of a treaty with the Sioux. Swearengen is reluctant to accept advice from Farnum while Trixie is away. Alma reconsiders her plans for her gold claim. Stubbs learns an important lesson from Tolliver.'),
(372, 9, 'No Other Sons or Daughters', '2004-05-16', 'Swearengen makes an effort to set up an informal government. Anna and Bullock discuss Ellsworth. Jane receives a job offer from Utter. Tolliver agrees to let Stubbs strike out on her own.'),
(372, 10, 'Mister Wu', '2004-05-23', 'Swearengen receives a double dose of irritation when a drug supply is stolen and bad news arrives from a nearby town. Rev. Smith is an unlikely customer at the Gem. Merrick hatches an idea for Deadwood''s first club.'),
(372, 11, 'Jewel''s Boot Is Made For Walking', '2004-06-06', 'Adams helps Swearengen out of a jam. Jewel seeks out Doc for treatment. Leon and Eddie go back to work for Cy. Alma''s father arrives from New York. The camp''s choice for a sheriff doesn''t please Bullock.'),
(372, 12, 'Sold Under Sin', '2004-06-13', 'In the first-season finale, Farnum and Tolliver take advantage of the arrival of a U.S. Army general. Adams teaches Clagett a thing or two about loyalty. Bullock reacts when Alma''s father states his intentions regarding her claim.'),
(373, 1, 'Into the Ring', '2015-04-10', 'Murdock''s vigilante crime fighting and his new law practice find equally dangerous challenges in a murder case tied to a corporate crime syndicate.'),
(373, 2, 'Cut Man', '2015-04-10', 'Murdock makes a near fatal error while trying to save a kidnapped boy, and finds an unlikely ally when he needs saving himself.'),
(373, 3, 'Rabbit in a Snow Storm', '2015-04-10', 'Murdock and Foggy take on a mysterious wealthy client, but Murdock is convinced that there''s more to the case than just the facts.'),
(373, 4, 'In the Blood', '2015-04-10', 'Two vicious Russian brothers working for Fisk strike back against Daredevil. Fisk moves to further consolidate his power in the criminal underworld.'),
(373, 5, 'World On Fire', '2015-04-10', 'Fisk moves forward with plans that threaten to rip Hell''s Kitchen apart. Murdock and Foggy take on a case helping tenants victimized by a slumlord.'),
(373, 6, 'Condemned', '2015-04-10', 'Daredevil finds himself trapped in the fallout of Fisk''s plan to take control of Hell''s Kitchen. Ben Urich digs closer to the truth.'),
(373, 7, 'Stick', '2015-04-10', 'An important figure from Murdock''s past reemerges seeking his help to battle a new enemy threatening Hell''s Kitchen.'),
(373, 8, 'Shadows in the Glass', '2015-04-10', 'While Murdock, Foggy and Karen''s mission becomes clearer, Fisk''s world spins further out of control in his battle for Hell''s Kitchen.'),
(373, 9, 'Speak of the Devil', '2015-04-10', 'When Fisk gains the upper hand, the goal to destroy him becomes even more difficult, while Daredevil faces his own demons.'),
(373, 10, 'Nelson v. Murdock', '2015-04-10', 'Murdock and Foggy''s relationship is put to the ultimate test while a new enemy against Fisk emerges.'),
(373, 11, 'The Path of the Righteous', '2015-04-10', 'Fisk and Murdock wrestle with the consequences of their chosen paths, while Ben and Karen get closer to Fisk''s true past.'),
(373, 12, 'The Ones We Leave Behind', '2015-04-10', 'Fisk seeks revenge while Karen is haunted by recent events. Daredevil makes a startling discovery about Fisk''s financing.'),
(373, 13, 'Daredevil', '2015-04-10', 'In the season finale, a boxed-in Fisk and a desperate Murdock, Foggy and Karen are forced to play their end games.'),
(374, 1, 'Entourage (Pilot)', '2004-07-18', 'Vincent Chase is a young, hot, up-and-coming actor living in Hollywood.  Tonight, he must attend the opening of his latest movie ''Head On''.   At the post-premiere party, Vince''s agent, Ari, hassles Eric about getting Vince to read the script for a possible new project.  Over breakfast, Vince says he''s not going to do ''Matterhorn'' on Eric''s advice.  The foursome goes to meet with the director where Vince impresses him so much that Ari calls later to tell him that they''ve offered $4 million for the part. While Turtle & Drama celebrate, Vince lets him know that Eric is not too enthused about the script.  Later, Ari & Eric share a rather confrontational dinner while discussing the future of their star''s career.'),
(374, 2, 'The Review', '2004-07-25', 'Ignoring the negative review from Variety, Vince ramps up his already excessive spending by leasing a new Rolls Royce. Ari urges Vince to get a ''real'' manager, causing a wounded Eric to do some soul searching.'),
(374, 3, 'Talk Show', '2004-08-01', 'Partying after a boxing match, Vince runs into Jimmy Kimmel, who immediately does his best to get Vince to commit to an appearance on his show the following night. Also at the party, Luke Wilson tells Turtle and Drama about his new home theater setup, planting the idea in their heads that they need an upgrade.'),
(374, 4, 'Date Night', '2004-08-08', 'Vince''s major work for the day is a stop at Big Boy''s Neighborhood, a local radio show.  As a result of the appearance, Vince secures a date for himself with Justine Chapin.\n\nWhile everybody gets ready for the night''s activities, Ari video conferences with Eric to tell him that matinÃ©e numbers for Vince''s movie have been ''less than stellar'' because it is in direct competition with the latest Pixar feature.'),
(374, 5, 'The Script and the Sherpa', '2004-08-15', 'The boys are less than pleased that Vince''s latest fling, Fiona, has over-stayed the 3-day rule that Vince instated long ago. Eric is re-introduced to an old acquaintance who may have just the script that Vince has been looking for: a story about a guy from Queens. Turtle tries to find a way around a weed drought in L.A.'),
(374, 6, 'Busey and the Beach', '2004-08-22', 'Drama prepares to meet his potential new agent and drags Turtle with him while Eric & Vince attend a special meeting. Later, the boys attend Gary Busey''s art opening where they bump into aspiring agent Josh Weinstein.'),
(374, 7, 'The Scene', '2004-08-29', 'Eric is concerned over the choice of director, an indie loose cannon named Billy Walsh, for Vince''s new film. Meanwhile, Drama lobbies for a supporting role, while Ari finds he can''t mix business with pleasure.'),
(374, 8, 'New York', '2004-09-12', 'As production on ''Queens Boulevard'' is about to begin, the boys are preparing to go to New York City for the next three months. Vince puts Turtle in charge of their ''bon voyage'' party, which proves to be a pain-in-the-neck for Eric later on. Meanwhile, Drama has a problem when an audition for a pilot conflicts with his small role in Vince''s new movie. Meanwhile, Eric wants a title commensurate with his responsibilities, but when a dinner meeting ends on a sour note, it looks like Vince''s entourage will be minus one.'),
(375, 1, 'Smoke Gets in Your Eyes', '2007-07-19', 'In 1960 New York City - the high-powered and glamorous ''Golden Age'' of advertising - Don Draper, the biggest ad man in the business, struggles to stay a step ahead of the rapidly changing times and the young executives nipping at his heels.'),
(375, 2, 'Ladies Room', '2007-07-26', 'Don continues to conceal his increasingly complicated personal life, even in the face of Roger Sterling''s invitation to open up. Meanwhile, Peggy pines for the absent Pete  still on his honeymoon  while fending off the advances of several of the men of Sterling Cooper.'),
(375, 3, 'Marriage of Figaro', '2007-08-02', 'Pete returns from his honeymoon, excited about his new marriage, but conflicted about his past encounter with Peggy. After his business relationship with Rachel takes an unforeseen turn, Don attends a party which further illuminates his increasing dissatisfaction with his present life.'),
(375, 4, 'New Amsterdam', '2007-08-09', 'Pete''s professional and personal lives become more complicated as he struggles to assert power in both. While facing pressure from his wife regarding a new apartment, he further alienates Don and endangers his own position at Sterling Cooper.'),
(375, 5, '5G', '2007-08-16', 'After Don wins an award, his photo is featured in Advertising Age. Don must deal with the fallout as the photo brings back a past he isnt ready to confront. Ken gets a short story published in The Atlantic Monthly, inciting jealousy among his colleagues and driving Pete to make an unorthodox request of his wife. Peggy overhears a startling conversation in the office and shares the secret with Joan.'),
(375, 6, 'Babylon', '2007-08-23', 'A taboo office romance is revealed. At a brainstorming session, Peggy proves to be more than a secretary, opening up new opportunities for her at Sterling Cooper. Meanwhile, Rachel faces her conflicted feelings for Don after he seeks out her advice on a new campaign.'),
(375, 7, 'Red in the Face', '2007-08-30', 'Roger joins Don for an evening of dinner and drinking, during which Roger''s behavior leads to a rift in their friendship. Though Don accepts his apology, there are further consequences for Roger. Pete faces trouble at home as he continues to struggle with the demands of his new marriage.'),
(375, 8, 'The Hobo Code', '2007-09-06', 'Don is tormented as pieces of his secretive past begin to haunt him. Peggy''s new success at work, and resulting boost in confidence, threaten her office relationship. Salvatore Romano gets a little too close with a client.'),
(375, 9, 'Shoot', '2007-09-13', 'A rival ad agency courts Don, involving Betty in their attempt to lure him from Sterling Cooper. As the presidential campaign heats up, the agency looks for new ways to counter the latest Kennedy ads. Tempers flare over Peggy.'),
(375, 10, 'Long Weekend', '2007-09-27', 'Don loses an account. Roger, stuck in the city for Labor Day weekend, attempts to cheer him up. Meanwhile, Joan has a night out on the town with her roommate.'),
(375, 11, 'Indian Summer', '2007-10-04', 'Peggy is given a difficult assignment. Roger''s work problems provide new opportunities for Don, and Pete grows more frustrated. Betty finds a new outlet for her growing dissatisfaction.'),
(375, 12, 'Nixon Vs. Kennedy', '2007-10-11', 'On election night, the Sterling Cooper staff pulls a rowdy all-nighter while watching the returns. Pete''s ambitions cause him to directly challenge Don. Don remembers his past as a soldier in the Korean War.'),
(375, 13, 'The Wheel', '2007-10-17', 'As Thanksgiving approaches, Don''s work responsibilities interfere with his domestic life. Peggy is given a new opportunity, provoking the ire of some of her colleagues. Betty makes a startling discovery.'),
